<figure class="mw-default-size mw-halign-right" typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:Andrzej_Sapkowski_-_Book_World_Fair_2010_Prague.jpg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/ec/Andrzej_Sapkowski_-_Book_World_Fair_2010_Prague.jpg/170px-Andrzej_Sapkowski_-_Book_World_Fair_2010_Prague.jpg" decoding="async" width="170" height="120" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/ec/Andrzej_Sapkowski_-_Book_World_Fair_2010_Prague.jpg/255px-Andrzej_Sapkowski_-_Book_World_Fair_2010_Prague.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/ec/Andrzej_Sapkowski_-_Book_World_Fair_2010_Prague.jpg/340px-Andrzej_Sapkowski_-_Book_World_Fair_2010_Prague.jpg 2x" data-file-width="2800" data-file-height="1980" /></a><figcaption><a href="/wiki/Andrzej_Sapkowski" title="Andrzej Sapkowski">Andrzej Sapkowski</a>, best known for <i><a href="/wiki/The_Witcher" title="The Witcher">The Witcher</a></i> book series</figcaption></figure>
<figure class="mw-default-size" typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:Strzemi%C5%84ski.jpg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0b/Strzemi%C5%84ski.jpg/170px-Strzemi%C5%84ski.jpg" decoding="async" width="170" height="113" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0b/Strzemi%C5%84ski.jpg/255px-Strzemi%C5%84ski.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0b/Strzemi%C5%84ski.jpg/340px-Strzemi%C5%84ski.jpg 2x" data-file-width="1200" data-file-height="800" /></a><figcaption><a href="/wiki/W%C5%82adys%C5%82aw_Strzemi%C5%84ski" title="Władysław Strzemiński">Władysław Strzemiński</a>, painter</figcaption></figure>
<ul><li><a href="/wiki/Daniel_Amit" title="Daniel Amit">Daniel Amit</a> (1938–2007), Israeli physicist</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Yehuda_Ashlag" title="Yehuda Ashlag">Yehuda Ashlag</a> (1885–1954), Rabbi</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Gra%C5%BCyna_Bacewicz" title="Grażyna Bacewicz">Grażyna Bacewicz</a> (1909–1969), composer</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Aleksander_Bardini" title="Aleksander Bardini">Aleksander Bardini</a> (1913–1995), theatre director and actor</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Andrzej_Bartkowiak" title="Andrzej Bartkowiak">Andrzej Bartkowiak</a> (born 1950), cameraman and film director</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Jurek_Becker" title="Jurek Becker">Jurek Becker</a> (1937–1997), writer</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Sylwester_Bednarek" title="Sylwester Bednarek">Sylwester Bednarek</a> (born 1989), high jumper</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Marek_Belka" title="Marek Belka">Marek Belka</a> (born 1952), politician, former Prime Minister</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Karolina_Bielawska" title="Karolina Bielawska">Karolina Bielawska</a> (born 1999), model and <a href="/wiki/Miss_World_2021" title="Miss World 2021">Miss World 2021</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Kazimierz_Brandys" title="Kazimierz Brandys">Kazimierz Brandys</a> (1916–2000), writer</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Artur_Brauner" title="Artur Brauner">Artur Brauner</a> (1918–2019), film producer</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Edward_G._Brisch" title="Edward G. Brisch">Edward G. Brisch</a> (1901–1960), industrial coding and classification expert</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Jacob_Bronowski" title="Jacob Bronowski">Jacob Bronowski</a> (1908–1974), writer, mathematician and Britain's leading academic TV figure of the 1970s</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Sabina_Citron" title="Sabina Citron">Sabina Citron</a> (1928–2023), Holocaust survivor, activist and author</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Bat-Sheva_Dagan" title="Bat-Sheva Dagan">Bat-Sheva Dagan</a> (1925–2024), Holocaust survivor, teacher, psychologist and author</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Karl_Dedecius" title="Karl Dedecius">Karl Dedecius</a> (1921–2016), translator</li>
